ould overcome caraxies and prince aymond would return to the city with prince damon's head not all the members of the green council favored the prince's bold stroke eamonn had the support of sir christian cole the hand and of sir tylen lannister but grand maester orwell urged him to send word to stormzand and add the power of house baratheon to his own before proceeding and ironrod lord jasper wilde declared that he should summon lord hightower and prince darren from the south on the grounds that true dragons are better than one the queen dowager favored caution as well urging her son to wait until his brother the king and his dragon sunfire the golden were healed so they might join the attack prince eamonn had no taste for such delays however he had no need of his brothers or the dragons he declared aegon was too badly hurt darren too young i karaxis was a fearsome beast savage and cunning and battle tested but vegard was older fiercer and twice as large septon eustis tells us that the kinslayer was determined that this should be his victory he had no wish to share the glory with his brothers not any other man nor could he be gain said for until agent ii rose from his bed to take up his sword again the regency and rule were eamon's true to his resolve the prince rode forth from the gate of the gods within a fortnight at the head of a host four thousand strong 16 days march to harren hall he proclaimed on the 17th we will feast inside black herons hall whilst my uncle's head looks down from my spear and across the realm obedient to his command jason lannister lord of casterly rock poured down out of the western hills descending with all his power upon the red fork and the heart of the riverlands the lords of the trident had no choice but to turn and meet him damon targaryen was too old and seasoned at badler to sit idly by and let himself be penned up inside the walls even walls as massive as harrenhal's the prince still had friends in king's landing and word of his