ns to all our leel lords summoning them to the defense of their true king when orwell hastened back to his chambers however he found four gold cloaks waiting for him one man muffled his cries as the others beat and bound him with a bag pulled over his head the grand maester was escorted down to the black cells queen allison's riders got no farther than the gates where more gold cloaks took them into custody unbeknownst to her grace the seven captains commanding the gates chosen for their loyalty to king again had been imprisoned or murdered the moment caraxies appeared in the sky above the red keep for the rank and file of the city watch still loved daemon targaryen the prince of the city who had commanded them of old queen ellison's brother sir gwayne hightower second in command of the gold cloaks rushed to the stables intending to sound the warning he was seized disarmed and dragged before his commander luther largent when hightower denounced him as a turn cloak sir luthor laughed diamond gave us these clothes he said and no gold no matter how you turn them he then drove his sword through sir wayne's belly and ordered the city gates open to the men pouring off the sea snake ships for all the vaunted strength of its walls king's landing fell in less than a day a short bloody fight was waged at the river gate where 13 high tower knights and a hundred minute arms drew off the gold cloaks and held out for nigh on eight hours against attacks from both within and without the city but the heroics were in vain for rhynirs soldiers poured in through the other six gates unmolested the sight of the queen's dragons in the sky above took the heart out of the opposition and king aegin's remaining loyalists hid or fled or bent the knee one by one the dragons made their descent sheepsteeler lighted a top of senya's hill silverwing and vermethor on the hill of rhaenys outside the dragonpit prince damon circled the towers of the red key before bringing caraxies down in the outer wa